1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 39-10-16 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to rotary traffic islands.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 39-10-16 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 39-10-16. One-way roadways and rotary traffic islands.
7 1. The director and local authorities with respect to highways under their respective
8 jurisdictions may designate any highway, roadway, part of a roadway, or specific lanes
9 upon which vehicular traffic shall proceed in one direction at all or such times as shall
10 be indicated by official traffic-control devices.
11 2. Upon a roadway so designated for one-way traffic, a vehicle shall be driven only in the
12 direction designated at all or at such times as shall be indicated by official
13 traffic-control devices.
14 3. A vehicle passing around a rotary traffic island must be driven only to the right of such
15 island.
16 4. After a vehicle enters a rotary traffic island, the vehicle may not exit from any position
17 within the rotary traffic island without first giving a signal of intention to exit the rotary
18 traffic island.
